# module: eng.table
# status: supported diagnostics, row-selection, and filter/require_one/join transform seeds; planned broader transform APIs
# purpose: domain-neutral promoted-table diagnostics, filters, row requirements, joins, derived columns, and schema helpers.
#
# Current implementation:
#   typed CSV promotion, source-hash provenance, row/column diagnostics,
#   parse/conversion counts, and time-axis coverage summaries are supported
#   through compiler/runtime built-ins for current examples. Deterministic
#   select_first_row(...) selection over promoted tables is supported as a
#   narrow artifact seed. Schema-aware `filter <table>` with `where { ... }`
#   predicates, `require_one <filtered_table>`, and `join <left> with <right>`
#   plus `on { left.key == right.key }` are supported as transform record
#   seeds. These appear in result.engres as
#   typed_payload.table_diagnostics[], typed_payload.table_selections[], and
#   typed_payload.table_transforms[].
#
# Planned helper vocabulary:
#   select columns
#   derive columns
#   sort rows
#   validate rows
#
# Review contract:
#   source schema, row counts, column counts, missing cells, parse failures,
#   conversion failures, time-axis coverage, selected row/reason, filter
#   predicate summaries, operation row counts, join keys, matched pair counts,
#   row-level diagnostics, and source spans.
#
# Non-goal:
#   this is not a general SQL replacement. Initial operations must stay
#   schema-aware and reviewable.
